{
  "text": "Medical Outcomes study 36-items short Form health survey (sF-36) Quality of life was assessed with the Medical Outcomes Study SF-36, [CITATION_1] a 36-item self-report measure. This survey assesses the following eight dimensions: vitality, physical functioning, bodily pain, general health perceptions, physical role functioning, emotional role functioning, social role functioning, and mental health. Reliability and validity have been found to be satisfactory and good, respectively. [CITATION_2] Patient health Questionnaire-9",
